 For the purposes of the section “identification evidence” includes any evidence that significantly relies on similarity of features: R v Whalen (2003) 56 NSWLR 454; [2003] NSWCCA 59;  BC200300878 . For the appropriate warning to be given in the case of identification evidence (
s 165(1)(b)
) see Craig v R (1933) 49 CLR 429 at 445; 7 ALJR 212 ; Davies v R (1937) 57 CLR 170 at 182; [1937] VLR 205 ; Kelleher v R (1974) 131 CLR 534 at 550; 4 ALR 450 ; Alexander v R (1981) 145 CLR 395 at 399; 34 ALR 289;  BC8100066 ; R v Clarke (1997) 97 A Crim R 414;  BC9705745 ; R v Bruno   (NSWCCA, 7 July 1997, unreported, BC9702877); R v Nguyen [2003] NSWSC 1068;  BC200307297 .
